    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="17"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 560.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> London,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 22, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>In regard to the deposition of Francis Glassbrook, referred to in your No. 775 of
                    the 2d instant, as obtained from Mr. Dudley, you will have received ere this my
                    despatch No. 555, a copy of another affidavit of the same person of a much more
                    decisive character, which I received from Mr. Dudley, and sent in to the British
                    government.</p>
                <p>I perceive from the newspapers of this morning that orders have been issued to
                    dismiss all persons from the naval reserve, and forfeit their allowances, who
                    have been enlisted in any of the rebel vessels.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
